n to me (my two types are both males). And finally your butterfly is precisely one of the two, M. daphnis (meleager), from which I separate my L. cormion as a distinct organism!

To recapitualte: You illustrate the wrong butterfly on your cover. This adds a gratuitous pictorial muddle to an obscure and subtle taxonomic problem. I cannot reconsider my objection.





Sincerely yours,

Vladimir Nabokov





TO: ROBIE MACAULEY





TL (XEROX), 1 p.





Montreux Palace Hotel

Montreux, Switzerland
